    </section>

    <section class="container">

        <p class="heading-prefix">Programming a multiplayer</p>
        <h2>Deterministic Simulation</h2>

        <p>Fighting games require very specialised multiplayer programming in order to reduce latency, as milliseconds count when it comes to player-verses-player combat. In order to achieve the lowest latency possible, we opted to use <a href="https://www.photonengine.com/quantum">Photon Quantum</a> for our game simulation.</p>

        <p>I implemented gameplay features to enhance the combat experience in the game, such as <b>picking up and throwing props</b> and <b>physics interactions with props</b>.</p>

        <p>Having the oppertunity to work first-hand with <b>Photon Quantum</b>, a deterministic entity-component system, inspired me to work on my own implementation of an <b>ECS</b> that utilises the <b>latest C# language features</b>.</p>


        <div style="height: 32px"></div>

        <Callout Type="primary">
            <Icon><SvgSprite Link="/icons.svg#icon-seal-check-fill" Alt="Check" /></Icon>
            <ChildContent>Working on this project inspired me to work on my personal projects. Some of them can be found below.</ChildContent>
        </Callout>

        <CardGrid>
            <Card href="/portfolio/fydarentities">
